g.text: a zero register or the stack
In A32 we had R0-R31, smaller registers were packed into larger ones. Now they are mapped one-to-one to the low-order bits of the bigger register.
In ARMv7, there were 32 64-bit registers D0, D1, ..., D31. In ARMv8, there are 32 128-bit registers V0, V1, ..., V31.
